The Minister of Higher Education, Science and Innovation, Dr Blade Nzimande, has released the outcome of the  Human Sciences Research Council’s (HSRC) second part of the public perception survey on the impact of the coronavirus (COVID-19) on South Africans. This follows the first survey conducted from Friday 27 March to Tuesday 31 March during which the council looked at how South Africans feel about the survey, what they understand, know and how they are reacting to the COVID-19 Emergency. Below is the full address: 